----- stdout -----
List all modules in the crate

Usage: crawk list [OPTIONS] [MODULE_PATH]

Arguments:
  [MODULE_PATH]  Module path to scope the listing (default: entire crate)

Options:
  -t, --include-tests    Include modules defined in `#[cfg(test)]` blocks (excluded by default)
  -s, --source           Show source file paths alongside module names
  -d, --depth <DEPTH>    Show only modules at depth ≤ N (inclusive filter, not truncation).
                         --depth 1: top-level only  (e.g. "parser")
                         --depth 2: top-level + one nesting level (e.g. "parser", "parser::visitor")
  -F, --filter <FILTER>  Filter modules by case-sensitive substring match on module path.
  -V, --visibility       Show module visibility (pub, pub(crate), pub(super), …)
  -f, --format <FORMAT>  Output format [default: plain] [possible values: plain, table]
  -h, --help             Print help (see more with '--help')

----- stderr -----
